{"id": "4440", "post": "<div class=\"post-4440 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry\" id=\"post-4440\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/simplenode-3month-256mb-ssd-kvm-vps-in-dallas-texas/\" rel=\"bookmark\">SimpleNode \u2013 $3/Month 256MB SSD KVM VPS in Dallas, Texas</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> September 28, 2013 @ 6:18 pm, by Liam</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"https://simpleno.de/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/simplenode1.png.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"screenshot litespeed-loaded\" title=\"simplenode\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/simplenode1.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a>Edward, from <a href=\"https://simplenode.co/\">SimpleNode</a>, has got two exclusive SSD KVM deals for LowEndBox readers located in Dallas, Texas (Incero). You will need to use the coupon code (<strong>SSDPROMO</strong>) to get the advertised prices.</p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>SSD KVM 256MB</strong><p></p><ul><li>256MB RAM</li><li>1 vCPU Core</li><li>4GB SSD Diskspace</li><li>500GB Bandwidth</li><li>1Gbit Shared Port</li><li>1 IPv4 Address</li><li>KVM/SolusVM</li><li>Coupon Code: <strong>SSDPROMO</strong></li><li>$3.00/ Month | <a href=\"https://simplenode.co/hostbill/cart/unmanaged-ssd-kvm/\">Order Link</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>SSD KVM 512MB</strong><p></p><ul><li>512MB RAM</li><li>1 vCPU Core</li><li>6GB SSD Diskspace</li><li>750GB Bandwidth</li><li>1Gbit Shared Port</li><li>1 IPv4 Address</li><li>KVM/SolusVM</li><li>Coupon Code: <strong>SSDPROMO</strong></li><li>$5.40/ Month | <a href=\"https://simplenode.co/hostbill/cart/unmanaged-ssd-kvm/\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>SimpleNode have been featured on LowEndBox a <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/?s=simplenode&amp;searchsubmit=Find\">handful of times</a> over the past year. They have been operating under the simplenode.co domain for 2 months now, but were using the simpleno.de domain for 12 months. These servers are on a node utilising the E3-1270v2 CPU and with 4x 256GB SSDs in RAID10 (on a \u201chigh end\u201d LSI card). If you require a custom operating system, simply open a ticket and they\u2019ll take care of it. SimpleNode have attracted some great reviews in the past; if you\u2019re a customer, how is your service?<br>\n<span id=\"more-4440\"></span><br>\nSimpleNode accept payments via Paypal and Bitcoin. Refunds are issued at their discretion. They reserve the right to refuse any refund request. Additional IPv4\u2019s can be purchased for $1.50/month. Still no IPv6, or ETA, due to provider (Incero). IRC is allowed for legitimate uses and VPNs are but for private use only. No Tor exit nodes or Adult content. Torrents are fine, however they will limit your disk I/O if you are abusing it. As usual, take a look at their <a href=\"https://simpleno.de/tos.php\">Terms of Service</a> before singing up.</p><p><strong>Network Information:</strong></p><p>Servers are located with Incero in Dallas, Texas.</p><p>Test IPv4: 23.29.127.98<br>\nTest File: <a href=\"http://lg.simpleno.de/100MB.test\">http://lg.simpleno.de/100MB.test</a><br>\nLooking Glass: <a href=\"http://lg.simpleno.de/\">http://lg.simpleno.de/</a></p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-con